snippet.textDisplay: Yes AT TIMES jones moved out of the way of Reyes combinations which is to be expected. But if you REALLY PAY ATTENTION you would notice jones had control over the center of the ring pretty much the whole fight and had Reyes moving backwards. Plus even though Reyes threw more strikes most did not land as cleanly was compared to jones who threw less but were more effective landing cleaner. Now combine that with jones defense his takedowns (although he didn’t get to do any damage off of the takedowns they still add points even if it’s just a little bit jones took Reyes down 3 times even if they were short instances he still gets rewarded some type of point for it.) and his effectively accurate striking and constant pressure/ring control it’s not surprising he EDGED The win. Stop looking at who has more punches thrown. How many of those punches landed? And of those landed did they do any damage? Were they partially blocked? As the fight wore on Reyes went from throwing combos to simple 1-2s with a lot less heat on them,. I’d give him rounds  1-2 and the FIRST HALF LF ROUND 3 round 3 was a draw in my opinion cause jones started to pick up tempo at the 2 and a half / 3 minute mark of that round. Round 4-5 obviously jones. Also the CHAMPIONSHIP ROUNDS ARE THE MOST CRUCIAL THEY REALLY SHOW WHAT YOU’RE MADE OF. Jones still looked fresh by the 5th Reyes looked winded. I’m not being biased but if you THINK YOU DID ENOUGH AGAINST A CHAMP then 10/10 you lost. In order to truly beat a champ you must not let it go to the judges. Reyes has everything in his arsenal to K.O jones by the 3rd but he didn’t and that’s why he did not win. ALSO NOT EVERYTHING IS DETERMINED ON THE AMOUNT OF PUNCHES YOU THROW. If you throw 100 punches and they all either barely connect or don’t do the damage you expect it too and I only throw 20-30 punches but I do more damage who won? 🤔

snippet.textDisplay: To me, championship rounds should be the first two or 3 before both fighters are tired. Honestly if anything the fight was a draw at best, I don't really think either man really won but if I had to choose, I would have definitely chosen Dominick Reyes in this fight to put the belt on. He knocked Jones off his ass the first round and gave it to him for two good solid rounds and made Jones bleed and swell. Also you can debate the 3rd one, and even debate the 4th one to some extent because what I saw was Reyes did well at the beginning of the 4th but faded off and Jones took control and definitely took control in the 5th round but never scared Reyes or have him pinned against the cage. I'd say this fight was a win for Reyes if I had to call it for a winner. Also, that judge needs fired who did the bad score  and needs fined. Jones did do a decent job tho, he fought Reyes on his terms and didn't dominate Reyes.
